      "value": "What is Global State?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Global state refers to data that is shared across multiple components in a Vue application."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use Global State?"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Share data across components**",
        "**Avoid prop drilling**",
        "**Maintain consistent data**",
        "**Simplify data flow in large apps**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Reactive Object"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "import { reactive } from 'vue';\n\nexport const store = reactive({\n  count: 0\n});"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Global State in Component"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "import { store } from './store';\n\nstore.count++;\nconsole.log(store.count);"
    },
